songs.title: In Excelsis
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
In excelsis, that's where you'll find me
Up above the rain cloud
Gliding past the blinding sunbeams
It's a new day
Sky blue, fresh air, ooh
I spent all of the daytime admiring the violent ocean
There's none certain and good things take time
I call out to the angels
They'll send me a sign to pray for
Little blue jay come to my window
I've been waiting all day
To watch you fly beneath the rainbow

[Verse 2]
Let me take you back to excelsis
Out where all of the angels
Stars and moon collide around you
To a new plane that no one else sees
Where I spend all the daytime
Watching the day go by

[Refrain]
Watching the time go by me
Watching the day go by
Watching the time go by me

[Chorus]
Rolling water, floral isles
Boy, my love will take you the tops of mountains
Feel the sweet escape
I know I'm gonna take you to a blissful cloud now
Let's get away, I know a place where no one ever
Will find you and me
Rolling water floral isles
Boy my love will take you the tops of mountains
Feel the sweet escape
I know I'm gonna take you to a blissful  cloud now
Let's get away I know a place where no one ever
Will find you and me
